Blockchain & Cryptocurrency Intermediate Course is a free, scholarship-based program by the Blockchain and Web3 Community Network (BWCN), designed for learners who have completed the beginner course or already have a basic understanding of blockchain and crypto concepts.

This course takes participants deeper into the world of decentralized technologies, exploring topics such as smart contracts, decentralized finance (DeFi), crypto wallets and security, tokenomics, NFTs, and an introduction to Web3 development tools and platforms. It’s designed to bridge the gap between foundational knowledge and practical application.

Open to all and offered for free through BWCN scholarships, this course empowers the next wave of African blockchain builders, creators, and innovators.
